.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
The \fBSoPointLightDragger\fP class provides interactive geometry for manipulating a point light source\&.
.PP
Here's how the dragger looks with its default geometry in the inactive state: 

 Screen Shot of Default Dragger
.PP
This dragger is well suited to use for setting up the fields of a \fBSoPointLight\fP node, as it provides geometry for the end-user to translate a point in 3D space\&.
.PP
The Coin library also includes a manipulator class, \fBSoPointLightManip\fP, which wraps the functionality provided by this class inside the necessary mechanisms for connecting it to \fBSoPointLight\fP node instances in a scenegraph\&.
.PP
\fBSee also:\fP
.RS 4
\fBSoPointLightManip\fP 
.RE
.PP

